                    <span>Although this book was written in 2003 and is more targeted to the beginner, it does offer some things of value:<P>- a review of third-party products available<BR>- tips on ensuring good music quality<BR>- other tips and tricks you're unlikely to find in Apple's documentation<P>After spending several hundred dollars on your iPod, I think it's reasonable to spend 3% or 4% of the purchase price to ensure that you're using it optimally.<P>I don't regret buying this book.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">90 pages of information in a 250 page package</div>
